The Chronicle Prosper Ndlovu in Lilongwe, Malawi ALL is set for the Zimbabwe-Malawi Solo Trade Exhibition, which begins here tomorrow under the theme “Fostering Trade Partnerships”. <img class="wp-image-556994 size-full" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/07/Trade-4.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/07/Trade-4.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/07/Trade-4-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Personnel putting final touches on stands The thre-day expo is being coodinated by the country’s trade development and promotion agency, ZimTrade in conjunction with the Malawi Investment and Trade Centre and the Zimbabwean Embassy in Malawi. <img class="alignnone wp-image-556989 size-full" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/07/Trade-1.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/07/Trade-1.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/07/Trade-1-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> About 30 local companies are expected to participate and some have already arrived and are pitching their stands (see pix) in readiness to engage with Malawian buyers.  More update to follow… 